Behavioral changes relative to upstream (beyond import paths):
  - crossref_client.py / openalex_client.py: a resolved DOI whose upstream
    record carries an EMPTY title no longer counts as DOI_MISMATCH (it made
    real ACL Anthology papers look fabricated); openalex additionally
    guards the 404/empty-record case.
  - _resolve.py: verdict-upgrading title-search hits are re-checked at
    0.85 similarity (the clients' internal 0.70 let short fabricated
    titles match different real works).

Vendored files (import paths adapted, otherwise verbatim):
  _text_similarity.py          <- scripts/_text_similarity.py
  crossref_client.py           <- scripts/crossref_client.py
  openalex_client.py           <- scripts/openalex_client.py
  semantic_scholar_client.py   <- scripts/semantic_scholar_client.py
                                  (SemanticScholarUnavailable moved in from
                                   scripts/contamination_signals.py)
  arxiv_client.py              <- scripts/arxiv_client.py
  reducer.py                   <- scripts/citation_verification_summary.py
  cache.py                     <- scripts/verification_cache.py
                                  (default path/env renamed to harness names)

Adapted files (derived from ARS designs/code):
  _resolve.py                  <- scripts/contamination_signals.py (excerpts;
                                  passport/ref_slug plumbing removed, cache
                                  threaded through)

Original files (this repository, but NC applies to the directory as a unit):
  __init__.py, bib.py, __main__.py

NOTE: because this directory is CC BY-NC 4.0, the Research-Agent-Harness
project as distributed includes non-commercial-only components. Commercial
use of the combined work is not permitted; remove this directory for a
pure-MIT build.
